<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-48-0311 </DOCNO><TEXT>In the Federal Republic of Germany up to 45% of primary energy is usedby private households and individuals. Ways of integrating energy efficiency(reduction of energy consumption) into local development have been collectedtogether in a few theses. They ask that better information be given tothe public and to private decision-makers about energy-saving techniques(energy consumption for heating per living-area, cogeneration system,condensation power station), exploitation of the benefits of communityheating installations (examples), energy-saving and additional expenses,the timely comparison of energy-efficient alternatives (diagrams) aswell as the inclusion of users and residents in the debate on energy-saving.Advice is given on the ADP-assisted graphic method of energy consumptioncontrol. (HWJ).</TEXT></DOC>